      "comment": "OPAL HUNTER (2) only beat a couple home last start but did draw wide. Much better served by this barrier and was good when he came from the back row and was held up when placed two back. Should get his chance from this barrier. A LITTLE SILENCE NZ (9) continues to race well having yet to miss a place in eight starts here since arriving from NZ, winning three of them. Draws wide but the consistency is hard to knock. ARTFUL MAJOR (5) kicked off the campaign with back-to-back wins then came from a 30m handicap and raced wide without cover but stuck on to place here last week. Go well again. WICKED HUSTLER (4) has claims off a win from the second line here two back.",
